    • Uses of Enums.TicketObjectType in com.sirqul.sdk.api.games

      Methods in com.sirqul.sdk.api.games with parameters of type Enums.TicketObjectType 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      SirqulResponse TicketApiBase.updateTicket(Long accountId, String appKey, Enums.TicketActionType actionType, Enums.TicketObjectType ticketObjectType, Long objectId, String purchaseCode, String receiptToken, String receiptData, Enums.PurchaseType purchaseProvider, List<Enums.PurchaseType> purchaseTypes, Boolean returnProfileResponse, Boolean includeProfileResponse, AppVersion appVersion)
      Save a ticket, used to redeem tickets or add tickets to the system

      Sample Params:
      deviceId=thangle-device&gameType=BOOPY&ticketObjectType =PROFILE&purchaseCode =myboopytestsubscription3&receiptToken=XXXXXXXXXXX &purchaseProvider=GOOGLE

      Things to keep in mind:
      1) When passing in a receipt token, a purchase provider is required!

      2) You can now purchase an item using the ticketObjectType/purchaseCode params or the ticketObjectType/objectId params.
      Either way you need to always send in the ticketObjectType, and either the purchaseCode or the objectId.

      3) Difference between receiptToken and receiptData:
      receiptToken is a unique identifier that can be use to quickly determine whether a purchase has already been processed or not.
      SirqulResponse TicketApiBase.updateTicketWithFileUpload(Long accountId, String appKey, Enums.TicketActionType actionType, Enums.TicketObjectType ticketObjectType, Long objectId, String purchaseCode, String receiptToken, String receiptDataFilePath, Enums.PurchaseType purchaseProvider, List<Enums.PurchaseType> purchaseTypes, Boolean returnProfileResponse, Boolean includeProfileResponse, AppVersion appVersion)
